 LINUS CHIBUIKE THE Chief Justice of Nigeria, Justice Tanko Muhammad, has sworn in eight new Justices of the Supreme Court. This brings the number of Justices of the apex court to 20. The swearing-in ceremony held on Friday at the Supreme Court in Abuja, the Federal Capital Territory. The CJN, who gave his remarks, after the eight justices took their oath of office and oath of allegiance to the Nigerian Constitution, warned the new justices to shun extraneous considerations while discharging their duties. The justices were recently elevated from the Court of Appeal bench. They include seven men and one woman â€“ five appointees from the North and three from the South. The newly inaugurated Justices are Lawal Garba (North West), Helen Ogunwumiju (South West), Abdu Aboki (North West), and M. M. Saulawa (North West). Others are Adamu Jauro (North East), Samuel Oseji (Souty South), Tijani Abubakar (North East), and Emmanuel Agim (South South). 